    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. Increase the timeout settings on the load balancer to 60 seconds.\n2. Set the timeout on the API endpoint to 60 seconds.\n3. Restart the load balancer and the API service to apply the changes.\n\nTo increase the timeout settings on the load balancer, you can use the following command:\n\n```\naws elb update-load-balancer-attributes --load-balancer-name my-load-balancer --load-balancer-attributes \"{\\\"LoadBalancerAttributes\\\":{\\\"ConnectionDraining\\\":{\\\"Enabled\\\":true,\\\"Timeout\\\":60}}}\"\n```\n\nTo set the timeout on the API endpoint, you can add the following code to your Express app:\n\n```\napp.use((req, res, next) => {\n  res.setTimeout(60000);\n  next();\n});\n```\n\nAfter making these changes, restart the load balancer and the API service to apply the changes. This should resolve the 504 gateway timeout issue and allow your deploy to proceed.",
